This paper deals with privacy-preserving mobile crowdsensing using blockchain and smart contracts. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of distributed systems and networks, which makes cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) another likely category. The paper also deals with mobile networks and wireless communication, which makes cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a possible category. The paper also involves the design of an auction mechanism, which makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with privacy and security issues related to mobile devices, which makes cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible category.
